--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b1552d282c800f140aa7402ea3f2ce5b, type: 3}
  m_Name: DefaultLanguage
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  DefaultLanguageName: PortugueseBrazilian
  LocalizationRelativePath: Assets/LocalizationLanguages
  BuildLocalizationRelativePath: Assets/LocalizationLanguages
  LocalizationTextList:
  - GETTING STARTED
  - 1. Open the <color=#FFC754>Localization Tool</color>.
  - 2. Navigate to the current settings file and delete it,  then go back to <color=#FFC754>Localization
    Tool</color> and click on the <color=#FFC754>Create</color> button to create
    your own Localization Setting Asset.
  - "3. Click these two buttons: the first will find all Text/TMP components in the
    current scene, and the second will find them in prefabs across the entire project.
    You\u2019ll need to open each scene individually and use the first button to
    locate all Text/TMP components in those scenes."
  - 4, Expand the <color=#FFC754>Text Components List</color> to view all the text
    components that were found. Click the <color=#FFC754>Setup All</color> button
    to configure them for localization.
  - 5, Click this button to add the text components to your settings file for localization.
  - '6, Open your scripts and locate all the hardcoded strings that require localization.
    Replace each string with <color=#A6D77D>Localization.GetString("Your string")</color>
    as shown in the example below:'
  - 7, Return to the <color=#FFC754>Localization Tool</color> and click on the <color=#FFC754>Find
    all texts in the scripts</color> button to locate the strings you just marked.
    After that, click on the <color=#FFC754>Add all checked results to [Localization
    Texts] List</color> button to include them in your localization settings file.
  - 8,Expand the <color=#FFC754>Localization Files</color> category, then set up
    your default language by clicking the button to navigate to the settings file.
    Once there, change the default language setting in the Inspector.
  - 9, Set up the relative path for the localization files. This path is relative
    to your <color=#A6D77D>Application.dataPath</color>. If you want a different
    path for the build, you can configure it in your code by calling <color=#A6D77D>Localization.ReadLocalizationFiles(_path)</color>.
  - 10, Click the <color=#FFC754>Create Default Language File</color> button and
    the <color=#FFC754>Create Meta File</color> button to generate the base localization
    files. After that, you can add additional languages using the <color=#FFC754>Add
    New Language</color> field.
  - 11, Whenever you added new texts to localization list, a green <color=#FFC754>Update</color>
    button will show behind the localization files, click them to update the files
    with the new texts you added.
  - 12, Add this line to the Awake method in a script within your first scene:<color=#A6D77D>string[]
    languages = Localization.ReadLocalizationFiles(localizationPath);</color>This
    will return the language names as a string array, which you can use to populate
    language selection options in your game.
  - Now that everything is set up, you can send those localization text files to
    AI for translation. Additionally, players can contribute to localization by modifying
    the existing text files or creating their own and placing them into the same
    folder. The system will automatically read all the text files in that folder
    and use the file names as the Language Name options.
  - "\u2018Workshop Friendly Localization\u2019 is the perfect solution for you!"
  - Or if you simply want to hand the text over to AI and get the localization done
    without any extra effort.
  - If you're planning to release your game on Steam and want to let players assist
    with localization.
  - If you feel this asset is helpful for your project, please give me review on
    AssetStore! Thank you!
  - 'Selected Language:'
  - 'We offer '
  - English
  - Simplify Chinese
  - Japanese
  - German
  - ' selectable languages in the demo.'
